{"cursor":"19161","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\n{{Infobox military unit |unit_name= Naval Research Laboratory |image=\n|caption=Emblem of the NRL |dates= 1923--present |country= United States\n|branch= Navy |type= Research and development |size= 2,562 civilian 110\nmilitary (2010) |command_structure= Office of Naval Research |garrison=  |commander1= [http://www.nrl.navy.mil/content.php?P=CO Capt Paul\nC. Stewart] |commander1_label= Commander |commander2=\n[http://www.nrl.navy.mil/content.php?P=DOR Dr. John A. Montgomery]\n|commander2_label= Director of Research |commander3= |commander3_label= }} The\n'United States Naval Research Laboratory' (NRL) is the corporate research\nlaboratory for the United States Navy and the United States Marine Corps and\nconducts a program of scientific research and development. NRL opened in 1923 at\nthe instigation of Thomas Edison. In a May 1915 editorial piece in the New York\nTimes Magazine, Edison wrote; \"The Government should maintain a great research\nlaboratory... In this could be developed...all the technique of military and\nnaval progression without any vast expense.\" In 1946, upon the\nestablishment of the Office of Naval Research, NRL was placed under the\ndirection of the Chief of Naval Research. NRL in its current form was created in\n1992 after the Navy consolidated existing R&D facilities to form a single\ncorporate laboratory. The NRL's budget was approximately $1.2 billion per year\nin 2008. http://www.nrl.navy.mil/content.php?P=DOR\n","linknr":545,"url":"United_States_Naval_Research_Laboratory","recorded":1362267799,"links":44,"instances":["fewc"],"pdf":["http://www.nrl.navy.mil/content_images/75highlights.pdf","http://www.nrl.navy.mil/content_images/75highlights.pdf","http://www.nrl.navy.mil/NewsRoom/images/little_book.pdf","http://www.nrl.navy.mil/NewsRoom/images/horizon.pdf"],"categories":["Military facilities in Washington, D.C.","United States Navy","United States military research 